modules.description: This module provides a `reload` function to open or refresh a URI in a web browser, with options to control background loading and URI prefixing. It works directly with string URIs and supports custom browser commands via the `Bos.Cmd.t` type. It is specifically useful for workflows requiring programmatic browser reloading, such as live-editing web content or testing API documentation and JavaScript applications built with `js_of_ocaml`.

This module defines command-line options for configuring web browser behavior, including selecting a browser, enabling a prefix, and running in the background. It works with command-line arguments using Cmdliner and integrates with the Webbrowser module's reload function. Concrete use cases include customizing browser launch commands and controlling reload behavior from the command line.
